The paper deals with distributed source coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves encoding and decoding of correlated sources, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of inner and outer bounds to characterize achievable rate regions is a common technique in information theory and optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the reconstruction of a function of X and Y, which is a problem in networked information systems (cs.NI).
